scopecontent.p:
The photographs reflect research for Paulson's various publications, including these titles: 
                     Hogarth's Graphic Works
                   (1965; revised 1970; 1989; 
                     Hogarth, His Life, and Times
                   (1971; 2nd edition 1972, abridged edition 1974); 
                     Rowlandson: A New Interpretation
                   (1972); 
                     Emblem and Expression
                   (1975); 
                     The Art of Hogarth
                   (1975); 
                     Popular and Polite Art in the Age of Hogarth and Fielding
                   (1979); 
                     Representations of Revolution
                   (1983, reprint 1987); 
                     Book and Painting: Shakespeare, Milton, and the Bible
                   (1983); and 
                     Breaking and Remaking: Aesthetic Practice in England, 1700-1820
                   (1989).
